-{zh-hans:'''马里波恩的约翰逊男爵约·约翰逊'''; zh-hk:'''約翰森，約翰森男爵'''; zh-tw:'''約瑟夫·埃德蒙·強森，[[馬里波恩|馬里波恩]]的強森男爵'''}-，{{post-nominals|country=GBR|size=100%|PC}}（{{lang-en|Joseph Edmund Johnson, Baron Johnson of Marylebone}}，{{bd|1971年|12月23日||}}），是一位[[英國|英國]][[保守黨_(英國)|保守黨]]籍政治人物。自2010年5月開始，他擔任[[奧平頓_(英國國會選區)|奧平頓]]選區的下議院議員<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/shared/election2010/results/constituency/d46.stm |title=Election 2010: Orpington |work=BBC News |accessdate=27 June 2010 |archive-date=2017-08-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170823105555/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/shared/election2010/results/constituency/d46.stm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。他曾擔任[[大學國務大臣|大學、科學、科研及創新國務大臣]]、英國運輸國務大臣<ref>Jonathan Amos [http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-32698484 ""] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-32698484 |date=20160219045326 }}, BBC News, 11 May 2015</ref>等職務。

約·約翰遜的兄長[[鮑里斯·約翰遜|鮑里斯·約翰遜]]於2019年7月[[英国首相|拜相]]後，他再度獲委任為[[大學國務大臣|大學、科學、科研及創新國務大臣]]，翌日獲委任為[[英國樞密院|樞密院]]成員。然而，上任僅一個多月便於同年9月初辭去國務大臣職務，且宣布不會競逐國會的連任<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.mingpao.com/ins/%E5%9C%8B%E9%9A%9B/article/20190905/s00005/1567690709947/%E3%80%90%E8%8B%B1%E5%9C%8B%E8%84%AB%E6%AD%90%E3%80%91%E7%A8%B1%E3%80%8C%E5%AE%B6%E5%9C%8B%E5%85%A9%E9%9B%A3%E5%85%A8%E3%80%8D-%E8%8B%B1%E9%A6%96%E7%9B%B8%E5%BC%9F%E8%BE%AD%E4%BB%BB%E5%9C%8B%E5%8B%99%E5%A4%A7%E8%87%A3%E5%85%BC%E8%AD%B0%E5%93%A1%E8%81%B7%E5%8B%99|title=【英國脫歐】稱「家國兩難全」　英首相弟辭任國務大臣兼議員職務|work=明報|date=2019-09-05|accessdate=2020-10-29|archive-date=2019-09-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190915142804/https://news.mingpao.com/ins/%E5%9C%8B%E9%9A%9B/article/20190905/s00005/1567690709947/%E3%80%90%E8%8B%B1%E5%9C%8B%E8%84%AB%E6%AD%90%E3%80%91%E7%A8%B1%E3%80%8C%E5%AE%B6%E5%9C%8B%E5%85%A9%E9%9B%A3%E5%85%A8%E3%80%8D-%E8%8B%B1%E9%A6%96%E7%9B%B8%E5%BC%9F%E8%BE%AD%E4%BB%BB%E5%9C%8B%E5%8B%99%E5%A4%A7%E8%87%A3%E5%85%BC%E8%AD%B0%E5%93%A1%E8%81%B7%E5%8B%99}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://inews.hket.com/article/2445091/%E3%80%90%E8%8B%B1%E5%9C%8B%E8%84%AB%E6%AD%90%E3%80%91%E7%B4%84%E7%BF%B0%E9%81%9C%E5%BC%9F%E5%BC%9F%E8%BE%AD%E8%81%B7%20%E8%8B%B1%E9%8E%8A%E6%80%A5%E5%8D%87%20%E4%BF%9D%E5%AE%88%E9%BB%A8%E6%94%BE%E6%A3%84%E4%B8%8A%E8%AD%B0%E9%99%A2%E6%8B%89%E5%B8%83|title=【英國脫歐】約翰遜弟弟辭職 英鎊急升 保守黨放棄上議院拉布|work=香港經濟日報|date=2019-09-05|accessdate=2020-10-29|archive-date=2019-09-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190914211615/https://inews.hket.com/article/2445091/%E3%80%90%E8%8B%B1%E5%9C%8B%E8%84%AB%E6%AD%90%E3%80%91%E7%B4%84%E7%BF%B0%E9%81%9C%E5%BC%9F%E5%BC%9F%E8%BE%AD%E8%81%B7%20%E8%8B%B1%E9%8E%8A%E6%80%A5%E5%8D%87%20%E4%BF%9D%E5%AE%88%E9%BB%A8%E6%94%BE%E6%A3%84%E4%B8%8A%E8%AD%B0%E9%99%A2%E6%8B%89%E5%B8%83}}</ref>；他稱辭職「因維繋家庭關係與國家利益相悖」，與首相兄長在[[英國脱歐|英國脱歐]]問題上存在分歧<ref>[https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/jo-johnson-boris-johnsons-brother-resigns-from-parliament_uk_5d70e1cee4b09bbc9efa44c9 Jo Johnson, Boris Johnson's Brother, Resigns From Parliament] {{Wayback|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/jo-johnson-boris-johnsons-brother-resigns-from-parliament_uk_5d70e1cee4b09bbc9efa44c9 |date=20220328052052 }}. HuffPost UK (5 September 2019).</ref><ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-49594793 PM's brother quits as Tory MP and minister] {{Wayback|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-49594793 |date=20190905103314 }}. BBC News (5 September 2019).</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|author=Jo Johnson|user=JoJohnsonUK|number=1169555292918571008|date=5 September 2019|title=It’s been an honour to represent Orpington for 9 years & to serve as a minister under three PMs. In recent weeks I’ve been torn between family loyalty and the national interest – it’s an unresolvable tension & time for others to take on my roles as MP & Minister. #overandout}}</ref>。

2020年7月，獲其兄長以[[保守黨黨魁_(英國)|保守黨黨魁]]身份提名晉爵，同年10月被封為-{zh-hans:'''馬里波恩的約翰遜男爵''';zh-hk:'''約翰森男爵''';zh-tw:馬里波恩的強森男爵}-，進入[[英國上議院|上議院]]議政<ref>{{cite web|url=https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/905975/Dissolution_Peerages_2019.pdf|title=Dissolution Peerages 2019|website=GOV.UK|language=en|access-date=2020-10-29|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103021620/https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/905975/Dissolution_Peerages_2019.pdf}}</ref>。

